description:
I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue:
1. Create a class in a subpackage, for example:

package subpackage;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

2. Compile the class using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior:
After compiling, a directory named "subpackage" is created under the existing "subpackage" directory. The compiled Test.class file is placed in the subpackage\subpackage directory.

When running the Java command, the following exception is thrown:

Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: subpackage/Test

Expected Behavior:
Running either of the following commands should fix the problem:
- ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java
- javac subpackage\Test.java
